Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: The New York City Board of Estimate
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ydthf
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 24 Mar 1989
The nightlife in New York City before the Second World War, and the 1989 ruling that the city's Board of Estimate is unconstitutional, as explored by Alistair Cooke.